<i>Where the hell did they go?</i>

263
00:19:33,040 --> 00:19:34,040
<i>They're just too fast!</i>

264
00:19:34,120 --> 00:19:36,040
What do we tell our boss now?

265
00:19:36,120 --> 00:19:38,440
God knows where their mom
took them and fled to.

266
00:19:38,520 --> 00:19:40,240
I'll deal with them later.

267
00:19:40,320 --> 00:19:41,680
They'll pay for this!

268
00:19:46,400 --> 00:19:47,480
Don't cry.

269
00:19:48,600 --> 00:19:50,800
Tawan, don't be scared.

270
00:20:10,600 --> 00:20:12,640
Can I hide in here with you?

271
00:20:14,640 --> 00:20:16,880
Who are you?

272
00:20:17,480 --> 00:20:19,120
My name is Thee.

273
00:20:20,560 --> 00:20:22,240
I'm mad at my mom,

274
00:20:23,160 --> 00:20:25,360
so can I hide in here too?

275
00:20:26,040 --> 00:20:28,800
You're mad at your mom too?

276
00:20:29,520 --> 00:20:30,480
Yes.

277
00:20:32,480 --> 00:20:33,800
My mom…

278
00:20:34,920 --> 00:20:36,400
She left me.

279
00:20:42,640 --> 00:20:46,400
Why is your mom so cruel?

280
00:20:46,480 --> 00:20:48,800
She's nothing like my mom.

281
00:20:51,800 --> 00:20:53,520
What's your name?

282
00:20:53,600 --> 00:20:55,880
My name is Kongkwan.

283
00:20:55,960 --> 00:20:58,720
Why are you hiding here?

284
00:20:59,320 --> 00:21:01,600
I'm sad because

285
00:21:01,680 --> 00:21:05,080
my mom loves someone else more than me.

286
00:21:05,720 --> 00:21:07,240
My friends are making fun of me.

287
00:21:07,320 --> 00:21:09,600
They say my mom's going to remarry.

288
00:21:09,680 --> 00:21:14,120
I don't want her to remarry.

289
00:21:15,000 --> 00:21:16,240
But I think

290
00:21:17,560 --> 00:21:19,520
your mom loves you the most,
no matter what,

291
00:21:20,840 --> 00:21:23,040
and she surely won't love
anyone more than you.

292
00:21:23,840 --> 00:21:26,760
You're lucky to have a mom.

293
00:21:28,320 --> 00:21:29,600
You're not like me.

294
00:21:31,480 --> 00:21:33,200
Mine's not with me anymore.

295
00:21:33,960 --> 00:21:36,680
Don't be sad.

296
00:21:36,760 --> 00:21:39,320
I'm sure she'll come back.

297
00:21:50,880 --> 00:21:52,480
It's getting late.

298
00:21:52,560 --> 00:21:54,400
Should we go see your mom?

299
00:21:55,160 --> 00:21:57,880
If she comes here and doesn't see you,

300
00:21:57,960 --> 00:21:59,480
she'll get sad.

301
00:22:00,080 --> 00:22:04,880
I don't want my mom to be sad.

302
00:22:04,960 --> 00:22:07,080
Then I'll take you to her, okay?

303
00:22:07,160 --> 00:22:11,040
You know my mom?

304
00:22:12,200 --> 00:22:13,160
Yes,

305
00:22:13,720 --> 00:22:15,520
I'm a friend of hers.

306
00:22:17,200 --> 00:22:18,320
Let's go.

307
00:22:24,920 --> 00:22:25,880
Okay.

308
00:22:27,920 --> 00:22:29,160
Mommy!

309
00:22:29,760 --> 00:22:30,880
Kongkwan!

310
00:22:34,080 --> 00:22:35,400
Where were you?

311
00:22:35,480 --> 00:22:37,600
I was so worried about you.

312
00:22:40,520 --> 00:22:44,760
I'm sorry for making you sad, Mommy.

313
00:22:47,480 --> 00:22:48,760
What happened, honey?

314
00:22:51,320 --> 00:22:52,160
Today,

315
00:22:53,080 --> 00:22:55,400
everyone's parents were here.

316
00:22:56,080 --> 00:22:58,360
She's probably sad

317
00:22:58,440 --> 00:23:00,120
that you didn't come see her work.

318
00:23:03,480 --> 00:23:04,960
I'm sorry, honey.

319
00:23:05,640 --> 00:23:06,480
It's my fault.

320
00:23:07,760 --> 00:23:08,880
Okay?

321
00:23:08,960 --> 00:23:12,280
You love me, right?

322
00:23:14,640 --> 00:23:15,880
Of course I do.

323
00:23:17,560 --> 00:23:19,280
I love you the most.

324
00:23:21,520 --> 00:23:25,400
I promise I won't make you sad again.

325
00:23:59,320 --> 00:24:00,720
SCUMBAG

326
00:24:09,200 --> 00:24:11,600
You asshole. You're not a real man!

327
00:24:11,680 --> 00:24:13,880
That's not what you said that night.

328
00:24:14,440 --> 00:24:17,280
All you said was how good I was.

329
00:24:17,880 --> 00:24:19,200
Asshole!

330
00:24:19,280 --> 00:24:20,920
The gift I sent you today

331
00:24:21,880 --> 00:24:23,480
was just to warn you

332
00:24:24,320 --> 00:24:25,960
to mind your own damn business.

333
00:24:26,960 --> 00:24:28,160
<i>Today's sex tape</i>

334
00:24:28,240 --> 00:24:30,720
may not be yours yet,

335
00:24:31,800 --> 00:24:33,360
but if you don't stop,

336
00:24:34,680 --> 00:24:36,000
I assure you

337
00:24:37,000 --> 00:24:38,960
there'll be even wilder ones.

338
00:24:42,040 --> 00:24:46,160
Next time, it won't be just you
I send the videos to.

339
00:24:47,960 --> 00:24:50,280
<i>Having all these nice, sexy videos</i>

340
00:24:50,920 --> 00:24:52,600
makes me want to show them off.

341
00:24:53,200 --> 00:24:54,400
I'm so sure

342
00:24:54,920 --> 00:24:58,320
the likes and shares will be crazy.

343
00:24:59,640 --> 00:25:01,800
<i>Just think about it.</i>

344
00:25:01,880 --> 00:25:04,600
Is risking your future

345
00:25:05,920 --> 00:25:07,080
really worth it?

346
00:25:08,280 --> 00:25:10,520
<i>Stay in your lane, Khim.</i>

347
00:25:11,160 --> 00:25:15,200
Stay out of my business,
and stay away from Ploy.

348
00:25:16,680 --> 00:25:17,520
<i>Okay?</i>

349
00:25:26,120 --> 00:25:28,120
Ploy. You're home?

350
00:25:59,840 --> 00:26:02,560
I need to go take care of something.

351
00:26:02,640 --> 00:26:03,600
I'll be home late.

352
00:26:03,680 --> 00:26:04,880
You can go to bed without me.

353
00:26:04,960 --> 00:26:06,720
You're coming home late again?

354
00:26:07,840 --> 00:26:12,000
Ever since we got married,
you never stayed home.

355
00:26:13,040 --> 00:26:15,760
Don't get mad. Come here.

356
00:26:19,840 --> 00:26:23,040
I already told you
I have something to take care of.

357
00:26:25,200 --> 00:26:27,520
What's that thing
you always need to take care of?

358
00:26:28,720 --> 00:26:30,560
You go out every night.

359
00:26:31,360 --> 00:26:34,760
And you're never back
until the morning after.

360
00:26:36,160 --> 00:26:37,400
Come on now.

361
00:26:38,520 --> 00:26:41,480
You're my wife, not my mom.

362
00:26:43,920 --> 00:26:45,840
If you keep being ridiculous

363
00:26:47,000 --> 00:26:48,840
till I can't stand you,

364
00:26:50,680 --> 00:26:52,600
I won't be this nice.

365
00:26:59,560 --> 00:27:00,680
Do you understand?

366
00:27:01,640 --> 00:27:02,960
My good girl.

367
00:27:06,160 --> 00:27:08,160
Keep being a good girl.

368
00:27:08,240 --> 00:27:09,840
You're way sweeter this way.

369
00:27:12,920 --> 00:27:16,240
This Saturday, I'm taking you
to visit your mom and dad,

370
00:27:17,360 --> 00:27:19,080
so we can have dinner with them.

371
00:27:20,280 --> 00:27:21,800
They must've missed you.

372
00:27:26,480 --> 00:27:27,880
When I say something,

373
00:27:29,840 --> 00:27:30,960
you answer.

374
00:27:32,200 --> 00:27:33,320
Understood?

375
00:28:34,680 --> 00:28:35,640
Ploy.

376
00:28:36,880 --> 00:28:37,920
I'm back.

377
00:28:48,320 --> 00:28:51,040
You're home at dawn every day.

378
00:28:52,160 --> 00:28:53,880
Just be honest with me.

379
00:28:54,560 --> 00:28:55,960
Are you seeing someone else?

380
00:28:56,040 --> 00:28:58,480
I already have you.

381
00:28:59,320 --> 00:29:00,600
How could I see someone else?

382
00:29:04,800 --> 00:29:08,440
Top, you reek of booze and cigarettes.

383
00:29:08,520 --> 00:29:10,120
Why don't you go shower first?

384
00:29:11,680 --> 00:29:14,080
Top, you're hurting me!

385
00:29:14,160 --> 00:29:16,040
You're lucky I even married you,

386
00:29:16,840 --> 00:29:18,120
yet you'd play hard to get?

387
00:29:19,280 --> 00:29:21,160
Why are you talking to me that way?

388
00:29:22,040 --> 00:29:25,360
If you didn't want to marry me,
why didn't you just tell Ma and Pa?

389
00:29:25,440 --> 00:29:26,880
Your mom

390
00:29:27,520 --> 00:29:28,800
really loves me.

391
00:29:29,840 --> 00:29:31,640
That's why she gave you to me so easily.

392
00:29:33,040 --> 00:29:35,320
She told me to take good care of you too.

393
00:29:36,200 --> 00:29:38,120
I'd better do what I was told.

394
00:29:38,800 --> 00:29:41,320
Top, Top, that hurts!

395
00:29:41,400 --> 00:29:43,120
Top! Top!

396
00:29:43,200 --> 00:29:45,960
I said it hurt!

397
00:29:50,960 --> 00:29:53,000
Top, I'm sorry.

398
00:29:53,600 --> 00:29:55,920
I won't say anything bad to you again.

399
00:29:56,440 --> 00:29:58,680
Please don't hurt me.

400
00:30:02,640 --> 00:30:04,280
Didn't you want me to come home?

401
00:30:04,360 --> 00:30:06,000
Well, here I am.

402
00:30:07,680 --> 00:30:08,920
So, take care of me.

403
00:30:10,360 --> 00:30:11,200
Top!

404
00:30:11,880 --> 00:30:12,920
Top!

405
00:30:13,720 --> 00:30:15,960
Don't hurt me, Top!

406
00:30:16,040 --> 00:30:17,040
Top…

407
00:30:19,080 --> 00:30:20,120
Top!

408
00:30:37,520 --> 00:30:40,320
<i>Don't you dare tell anyone</i>
<i>about what's going on at home,</i>

409
00:30:40,840 --> 00:30:42,440
<i>or you'll regret it.</i>

410
00:31:09,280 --> 00:31:12,000
You're not mad at me anymore, right?

411
00:31:14,800 --> 00:31:16,640
I never was mad at you.

412
00:31:17,720 --> 00:31:19,760
I was the one who broke your promise.

413
00:31:20,640 --> 00:31:22,080
It's okay.

414
00:31:22,160 --> 00:31:25,280
Uncle Thee told me you love me the most,

415
00:31:25,360 --> 00:31:28,960
and I'm luckier than him
to still have my mom.

416
00:31:29,040 --> 00:31:32,800
Unlike me, his mom left him.

417
00:31:36,360 --> 00:31:37,600
Okay.

418
00:31:37,680 --> 00:31:39,920
But you have to promise me

419
00:31:40,000 --> 00:31:41,760
you won't run away from me again.

420
00:31:42,400 --> 00:31:44,480
- Okay?
- Okay, I promise.

421
00:31:45,160 --> 00:31:46,320
And what else?

422
00:31:49,920 --> 00:31:51,040
Let me kiss your forehead.

423
00:31:52,920 --> 00:31:55,320
Come on. Go to sleep.

424
00:31:57,440 --> 00:31:58,720
Good night.

425
00:31:59,400 --> 00:32:00,400
Good night.

426
00:32:14,560 --> 00:32:17,240
Poor little girl. She must've been tired.

427
00:32:17,320 --> 00:32:18,480
Yeah.

428
00:32:19,760 --> 00:32:21,400
Mr. Pat's here, Mook.

429
00:32:40,000 --> 00:32:41,240
I'm sorry, Mook.

430
00:32:42,720 --> 00:32:45,400
If I'd kept waiting for you,
it wouldn't have happened.

431
00:32:46,640 --> 00:32:48,240
Don't blame yourself, Boss.

432
00:32:48,800 --> 00:32:51,960
It's entirely my fault
for not caring about her feelings.

433
00:32:58,720 --> 00:33:01,360
How's Kongkwan doing?

434
00:33:02,920 --> 00:33:04,160
She's asleep.

435
00:33:04,840 --> 00:33:06,560
She's feeling better now.

436
00:33:07,360 --> 00:33:10,280
What about you? Are you okay?

437
00:33:14,520 --> 00:33:15,960
Not really.

438
00:33:19,160 --> 00:33:21,480
I need better self-management.

439
00:33:23,720 --> 00:33:26,640
I need to rearrange my life's priorities.

440
00:33:33,160 --> 00:33:34,840
I've decided, Boss.

441
00:33:36,000 --> 00:33:38,720
She's the most important thing in my life.

442
00:33:41,240 --> 00:33:43,840
I'll have to trade something

443
00:33:44,920 --> 00:33:48,200
to keep what I value the most in my life.

444
00:33:50,200 --> 00:33:53,000
Are you talking about Mr. Thee?

445
00:34:28,120 --> 00:34:30,199
<i>I'm sad because</i>

446
00:34:30,280 --> 00:34:33,800
my mom loves someone else more than me.

447
00:34:34,560 --> 00:34:35,960
My friends are making fun of me.

448
00:34:36,040 --> 00:34:38,000
They say my mom's going to remarry.

449
00:34:38,520 --> 00:34:42,560
I don't want her to remarry.

450
00:34:42,639 --> 00:34:47,639
<i>I don't want my mom to be sad.</i>

451
00:35:16,080 --> 00:35:17,440
How's Kongkwan doing?

452
00:35:20,560 --> 00:35:21,600
She's doing better now.

453
00:35:23,880 --> 00:35:25,920
Yesterday, she was probably very sad

454
00:35:26,000 --> 00:35:27,760
that I broke my promise.

455
00:35:31,040 --> 00:35:32,400
I wanted to thank you

456
00:35:33,120 --> 00:35:35,200
for helping me find her yesterday

457
00:35:37,280 --> 00:35:39,040
and to thank you

458
00:35:41,160 --> 00:35:43,160
for everything you've done.

459
00:35:48,920 --> 00:35:50,640
You said

460
00:35:51,960 --> 00:35:54,000
you were waiting for my answer.

461
00:35:54,080 --> 00:35:56,360
Please don't reject me just yet.

462
00:35:58,080 --> 00:36:00,920
No matter now or later,
my answer stays the same.

463
00:36:02,000 --> 00:36:04,480
What happened yesterday reminded me

464
00:36:05,320 --> 00:36:07,320
just how important she is to me.

465
00:36:10,400 --> 00:36:12,600
I don't want to make her sad again.

466
00:36:16,120 --> 00:36:18,120
Please don't waste your time with me.

467
00:36:28,800 --> 00:36:30,560
Thank you for understanding.

468
00:37:00,640 --> 00:37:02,320
Is something wrong, Mr. Thee?

469
00:37:02,400 --> 00:37:04,560
Ms. Mook looked stressed.

470
00:37:17,480 --> 00:37:20,960
Is this a sign that we're losing our jobs?

471
00:37:21,040 --> 00:37:22,480
No way!

472
00:37:23,080 --> 00:37:24,760
I just signed up for a facelift.

473
00:37:24,840 --> 00:37:27,000
I'm still paying it off.
I can't go broke now!

474
00:37:36,320 --> 00:37:37,360
Mr. Pitak.

475
00:37:39,200 --> 00:37:41,800
- Yes?
- What happened?

476
00:37:42,600 --> 00:37:45,240
Why is Mr. Thee's stuff being moved out?

477
00:37:45,320 --> 00:37:47,080
It was Mr. Thee's orders.

478
00:37:48,280 --> 00:37:51,280
From now on, he'll be working
at the hotel like before.

479
00:37:51,360 --> 00:37:52,720
Should there be any meetings,

480
00:37:53,400 --> 00:37:55,880
we'll have you attend them at the hotel.

481
00:37:57,040 --> 00:38:03,640
Okay. So, that means
we'll still be working together, right?

482
00:38:05,120 --> 00:38:06,160
Yes.

483
00:38:14,040 --> 00:38:16,240
- If you'll excuse me.
- See you later.

484
00:38:20,800 --> 00:38:21,920
Hey,

485
00:38:22,000 --> 00:38:24,120
I think something must've happened.

486
00:38:26,200 --> 00:38:27,800
Did Mook and Mr. Thee fight?

487
00:38:31,760 --> 00:38:34,720
If they really fought,

488
00:38:35,400 --> 00:38:38,480
what about our story with them
being a couple?

489
00:38:38,560 --> 00:38:39,560
What do we do?

490
00:38:41,560 --> 00:38:42,920
Oh, right.

491
00:38:46,960 --> 00:38:48,400
<i>You've talked to Mr. Thee?</i>

492
00:38:49,240 --> 00:38:52,360
Yes, but don't worry.

493
00:38:52,440 --> 00:38:55,320
I'll make sure it won't affect our work.

494
00:38:56,280 --> 00:38:58,440
If our company is affected in any way,

495
00:38:59,000 --> 00:39:00,280
I'll gladly quit.

496
00:39:01,560 --> 00:39:03,280
Don't say that as if we're strangers.

497
00:39:04,520 --> 00:39:06,640
I'd never leave you just because of this.

498
00:39:06,720 --> 00:39:09,640
And if something happens
because of your decision,

499
00:39:09,720 --> 00:39:11,560
I'm ready to accept it too.

500
00:39:13,560 --> 00:39:14,920
Thank you, Boss.

501
00:39:15,600 --> 00:39:18,880
I'm sure Mr. Thee won't mix his work
with his personal life, Mook.

502
00:39:20,520 --> 00:39:21,880
What I'm more worried about

503
00:39:22,480 --> 00:39:25,040
is the news about you and him.

504
00:39:31,120 --> 00:39:32,920
I'll go talk to that reporter.

505
00:39:34,480 --> 00:39:35,960
It's no use, Mook.

506
00:39:37,280 --> 00:39:39,800
She won't leave us alone for sure.

507
00:39:42,760 --> 00:39:44,120
Also,

508
00:39:45,040 --> 00:39:47,680
I'm partly responsible for this too.

509
00:39:48,760 --> 00:39:50,800
I'll try talking to Prao again.

510
00:39:52,800 --> 00:39:55,640
I'm sorry for causing you trouble.

511
00:40:03,320 --> 00:40:05,920
I took care of everything as you asked.

512
00:40:06,000 --> 00:40:09,840
I've moved out your belongings
and dealt with the reporter.

513
00:40:09,920 --> 00:40:11,360
<i>I can't help you with that.</i>

514
00:40:11,440 --> 00:40:15,280
I'm a reporter.
It's my duty to present the truth.

515
00:40:15,800 --> 00:40:17,360
Please let Mr. Thee know

516
00:40:17,440 --> 00:40:20,600
no matter what he does,
he can't esape the truth.

517
00:40:21,360 --> 00:40:22,760
You're a reporter.

518
00:40:24,240 --> 00:40:26,800
Of course you have to present
everything as it is.

519
00:40:36,600 --> 00:40:39,440
You covered the wastewater treatment story
in a community, right?

520
00:40:43,440 --> 00:40:45,720
If you stop writing news
about Mr. Thee and Ms. Mook,

521
00:40:46,760 --> 00:40:48,160
no one will know about this.

522
00:40:48,840 --> 00:40:49,880
Are you threatening me?

523
00:40:49,960 --> 00:40:52,160
In my entire time working with Mr. Thee,

524
00:40:53,000 --> 00:40:54,720
he's never threatened anyone.

525
00:40:54,800 --> 00:40:57,240
If your agency found out

526
00:40:57,800 --> 00:40:58,840
you falsified the story

527
00:40:58,920 --> 00:41:01,440
about the corruption
in the project's development,

528
00:41:02,280 --> 00:41:05,400
you might want to start
looking for a new job.

529
00:41:09,320 --> 00:41:12,320
I want the files of the photo
you brought to the conference that day

530
00:41:12,840 --> 00:41:14,400
and also all the photos

531
00:41:14,480 --> 00:41:17,560
taken by the people you sent
to follow Mr. Thee and Ms. Mook.

532
00:41:22,440 --> 00:41:23,560
Thank you.

533
00:41:24,120 --> 00:41:27,640
I don't want there to be any stories
that'll defame me and Mook

534
00:41:29,240 --> 00:41:31,080
because I don't want her daughter

535
00:41:31,720 --> 00:41:33,760
to be sad about things like this again.

536
00:41:36,000 --> 00:41:38,520
You seem to care a lot about Ms. Mook.

537
00:41:39,160 --> 00:41:40,000
I do,

538
00:41:41,080 --> 00:41:42,440
because I got to see

539
00:41:43,040 --> 00:41:46,800
just how great the love
Mook has for her daughter is.

540
00:41:48,440 --> 00:41:50,880
I want to protect their feelings.

541
00:41:51,600 --> 00:41:53,560
Well, I hope you haven't forgotten

542
00:41:54,840 --> 00:41:57,280
that you already have someone.

543
00:42:01,280 --> 00:42:02,880
I'll deal with that myself,

544
00:42:03,520 --> 00:42:07,480
but I want you to handle the issue
at Ms. Mook's daughter's school.

545
00:42:08,960 --> 00:42:09,960
Of course.

546
00:42:15,000 --> 00:42:17,600
{\an8}CHADCHAI

547
00:42:20,280 --> 00:42:21,680
That's all. Thank you.

548
00:42:22,280 --> 00:42:23,120
You're welcome.

549
00:42:32,920 --> 00:42:35,040
Hello, Mr. Chadchai.

550
00:42:48,360 --> 00:42:50,800
Khim, something bad happened.

551
00:42:52,000 --> 00:42:54,640
- What's up?
- Did you hear about Preaw?

552
00:42:55,360 --> 00:42:56,560
She's hospitalized?

553
00:42:56,640 --> 00:42:59,960
They say she got beaten so badly,
she was hospitalized.

554
00:43:00,720 --> 00:43:03,120
So the news about her
being abused is true.

555
00:43:03,200 --> 00:43:07,440
I'm sure it was that guy
at the birthday party.

556
00:43:10,240 --> 00:43:12,320
- But the other day, I still--
- What is it?

557
00:43:13,000 --> 00:43:13,960
Did you go see her?

558
00:43:15,120 --> 00:43:16,360
Nothing.

559
00:43:16,440 --> 00:43:19,560
I meant at the party,
they still seemed fine.

560
00:43:20,840 --> 00:43:23,960
Her friend said
she couldn't take it anymore,

561
00:43:24,040 --> 00:43:26,280
so she broke up with him,
but he wouldn't let her.

562
00:43:26,360 --> 00:43:29,280
Then, they had a big fight,
and he hurt her.

563
00:43:30,440 --> 00:43:33,920
You really can't judge a book
by its cover.

564
00:43:49,240 --> 00:43:50,160
Come on in.

565
00:43:57,080 --> 00:43:57,960
Time for you break.

566
00:44:01,280 --> 00:44:02,200
Thank you.

567
00:44:16,400 --> 00:44:17,800
Get it together, Mook.

568
00:44:19,360 --> 00:44:21,000
Come on. Get it together.

569
00:45:04,560 --> 00:45:06,240
Hello.

570
00:45:08,880 --> 00:45:10,400
I bought some desserts for you.

571
00:45:11,120 --> 00:45:12,440
This shop makes the best desserts.

572
00:45:12,520 --> 00:45:13,760
Here you go.

573
00:45:16,440 --> 00:45:17,640
Sorry, I can't accept this.

574
00:45:18,240 --> 00:45:19,200
You shouldn't have.

575
00:45:20,560 --> 00:45:22,000
Please, take it.

576
00:45:22,080 --> 00:45:24,120
We just wanted to spread some kindness.

577
00:45:25,680 --> 00:45:29,240
In the past, if we've done you any wrong,

578
00:45:29,760 --> 00:45:31,120
please forget about it.

579
00:45:31,720 --> 00:45:34,200
After all, our kids are friends.

580
00:45:35,520 --> 00:45:39,480
That's right. From now on,
we'll make sure to zip it.

581
00:45:39,560 --> 00:45:43,720
We won't say or do anything
to make Kongkwan uncomfortable.

582
00:45:46,560 --> 00:45:48,000
What happened?

583
00:45:48,560 --> 00:45:50,520
Last time we met, you two still hated me.

584
00:45:51,360 --> 00:45:54,920
We heard about Kongkwan
going missing the other day,

585
00:45:55,920 --> 00:45:57,480
and we felt bad

586
00:45:57,560 --> 00:46:00,080
that she was upset partly because of us.

587
00:46:01,200 --> 00:46:03,880
If our kids went missing,

588
00:46:03,960 --> 00:46:05,640
it would break our hearts too.

589
00:46:09,200 --> 00:46:10,680
Mommy!

590
00:46:11,760 --> 00:46:12,680
Are you tired?

591
00:46:15,000 --> 00:46:16,680
Thank you for understanding.

592
00:46:17,200 --> 00:46:18,880
If you'll excuse me. Let's go.

593
00:46:18,960 --> 00:46:20,400
Oh, Ms. Mook.

594
00:46:22,720 --> 00:46:25,360
- Please accept it.
- Please.

595
00:46:25,440 --> 00:46:26,560
Please, Ms. Mook.

596
00:46:26,640 --> 00:46:27,600
Please.

597
00:46:27,680 --> 00:46:28,760
Thank you.

598
00:46:29,920 --> 00:46:32,200
Let's go, honey. Did you have fun today?

599
00:46:51,880 --> 00:46:54,880
We really didn't want things
to get this far.

600
00:46:55,920 --> 00:46:56,760
That's right.

601
00:46:56,840 --> 00:47:00,200
We really didn't expect Ms. Prao
to send the photos to that reporter.

602
00:47:00,280 --> 00:47:03,200
Mr. Thee will let you off this time…

603
00:47:06,240 --> 00:47:07,560
but on one condition.

604
00:47:08,880 --> 00:47:13,160
Don't cause any trouble
for Ms. Mook and her daughter again.

605
00:47:14,280 --> 00:47:16,880
I hope we won't have to meet
like this again.

606
00:47:19,560 --> 00:47:20,520
You can keep them.

607
00:47:20,600 --> 00:47:21,800
Keep them as souvenirs.

608
00:47:21,880 --> 00:47:23,240
I have the files already.

609
00:47:30,720 --> 00:47:33,920
We're lucky they're not suing us.

610
00:47:34,600 --> 00:47:38,200
I can't imagine if we had
to take it all the way to court.

611
00:47:38,280 --> 00:47:40,840
But this means Mr. Thee

612
00:47:40,920 --> 00:47:42,960
must really care about Kongkwan's mom.

613
00:47:43,720 --> 00:47:46,360
He loves her, obviously.

614
00:47:46,440 --> 00:47:47,640
Mom!

615
00:47:47,720 --> 00:47:48,560
- Hey, kids!
- Hi!

616
00:47:51,880 --> 00:47:53,440
Guys,

617
00:47:53,520 --> 00:47:58,320
from now on, don't pick a fight
with Kongkwan again, got it?

618
00:47:59,080 --> 00:48:01,800
Well, you're the one
who told us that her mom

619
00:48:01,880 --> 00:48:04,120
is a bad person and to stay away from her.

620
00:48:10,000 --> 00:48:11,360
Let's go home, honey.

621
00:48:11,440 --> 00:48:13,400
Let's go. Come on.

622
00:48:14,920 --> 00:48:15,840
Come on.

623
00:48:15,920 --> 00:48:17,560
You good? Do you want me to hold that?

624
00:48:17,640 --> 00:48:18,880
Good job.

625
00:48:21,560 --> 00:48:24,040
Our hotel's doing very bad right now.

626
00:48:24,680 --> 00:48:27,760
We need to hurry
and do something, Mrs. Narin.

627
00:48:28,680 --> 00:48:29,880
It's true.

628
00:48:29,960 --> 00:48:32,560
We're barely getting any guests.

629
00:48:33,160 --> 00:48:36,120
It'll probably stay this slow
for quite a while.

630
00:48:36,200 --> 00:48:38,040
The other hotels that can't survive

631
00:48:38,120 --> 00:48:40,600
have already started to shut down.

632
00:48:41,120 --> 00:48:45,160
But I don't think our hotel
will need to shut down too.

633
00:48:47,640 --> 00:48:49,480
What do you mean, Mr. Chadchai?

634
00:48:50,120 --> 00:48:52,360
It'll be hard to get
a bank loan right now.

635
00:48:53,000 --> 00:48:56,680
To be honest,
we're already badly overdrawn.

636
00:48:56,760 --> 00:48:59,960
There's an investor
who's interested in our hotel.

637
00:49:00,480 --> 00:49:01,840
I'll go talk to him.

638
00:49:01,920 --> 00:49:04,880
So we'll need a stockholder to help us?

639
00:49:06,560 --> 00:49:08,840
It's still better than shutting down.

640
00:49:11,480 --> 00:49:14,240
Right now, we can still
support our employees,

641
00:49:15,200 --> 00:49:17,040
but if this continues,

642
00:49:17,760 --> 00:49:19,280
we won't be able to sustain them

643
00:49:19,960 --> 00:49:21,600
or even our hotel.

644
00:49:31,280 --> 00:49:32,560
COULDN'T COPE! HOTEL AFFECTED BY COVID
DECIDES TO SHUTDOWN

645
00:49:32,640 --> 00:49:35,000
NARIN BEACH RESORT AFFECTED BY COVID
COULDN'T COPE, SHUTS DOWN

646
00:49:46,840 --> 00:49:48,240
<i>Don't worry, Mr. Thee.</i>

647
00:49:48,320 --> 00:49:51,480
I think you'll get what you want very soon

648
00:49:51,560 --> 00:49:54,920
because the hotel's been doing
very bad lately.

649
00:49:55,880 --> 00:49:59,040
Good. I'll leave it to you, Mr. Chadchai.

650
00:49:59,120 --> 00:50:00,160
Of course.

651
00:50:01,280 --> 00:50:03,480
How many shares
would you like to purchase?

652
00:50:03,560 --> 00:50:05,840
As many as possible.

653
00:50:06,680 --> 00:50:08,680
In fact, I'd like all of it.

654
00:50:12,080 --> 00:50:15,880
You probably saw
that our hotel is a good investment.

655
00:50:16,520 --> 00:50:17,960
I've been waiting for this moment.

656
00:50:18,720 --> 00:50:20,440
I need an answer very soon.

657
00:50:22,160 --> 00:50:23,800
I hope you remember our deal.

658
00:50:24,400 --> 00:50:28,960
Don't worry, I'll reward you
according to the shares I get.

659
00:50:29,040 --> 00:50:29,880
How about that?

660
00:50:44,880 --> 00:50:47,640
You have a meeting
about the couple campaign today, Mr. Thee.

661
00:50:47,720 --> 00:50:50,080
A Round Trip will attend it too.

662
00:50:52,280 --> 00:50:53,640
Will Ms. Mook be attending?

663
00:50:53,720 --> 00:50:55,280
Her name wasn't listed, sir.

664
00:50:58,680 --> 00:51:01,080
Ms. Usa wanted to treat you to lunch.

665
00:51:01,160 --> 00:51:02,800
She said she wanted to speak with you.

666
00:51:13,360 --> 00:51:15,320
You haven't eaten all morning?

667
00:51:15,400 --> 00:51:17,080
I'm not very hungry.

668
00:51:18,640 --> 00:51:20,200
You can have someone take it out.

669
00:51:35,200 --> 00:51:37,760
Mook, are you sure you're fine with this?

670
00:51:37,840 --> 00:51:40,800
I could've come alone, you know.

671
00:51:40,880 --> 00:51:42,000
It wouldn't be right, Whan.

672
00:51:42,080 --> 00:51:44,560
This is about work. I can differentiate.

673
00:51:47,640 --> 00:51:51,040
So, are you and Mr. Thee fighting?

674
00:52:05,600 --> 00:52:06,800
Mook!

675
00:52:07,760 --> 00:52:10,200
I thought you weren't attending.

676
00:52:10,880 --> 00:52:12,240
I'm glad you came.

677
00:52:15,000 --> 00:52:17,440
Hello, Mook. Are you here for a meeting?

678
00:52:17,520 --> 00:52:20,240
I'm just heading to lunch with Mr. Thee.

679
00:52:22,080 --> 00:52:23,040
Go ahead.

680
00:52:23,800 --> 00:52:24,880
There's still time.

681
00:52:25,400 --> 00:52:26,600
Let's have lunch together, Mook.

682
00:52:27,400 --> 00:52:28,280
It's okay.

683
00:52:28,360 --> 00:52:29,960
Please go ahead. I'm not hungry.

684
00:52:35,120 --> 00:52:37,160
But it sounds like
Ms. Whan's hungry, Mook.

685
00:52:39,720 --> 00:52:42,120
Stop thinking about it. Just come with me.

686
00:52:42,200 --> 00:52:43,680
Let's go. Come on, Ms. Whan.

687
00:52:46,600 --> 00:52:47,720
Well…

688
00:52:48,320 --> 00:52:50,360
Wait for me, Mr. Thee!

689
00:53:12,920 --> 00:53:15,160
You wanted to speak with me
about something?

690
00:53:16,640 --> 00:53:18,040
It's nothing, really.

691
00:53:18,120 --> 00:53:20,680
I've read some bad news about you,

692
00:53:20,760 --> 00:53:23,440
so I was worried about you.

693
00:53:25,760 --> 00:53:27,000
About me and Ms. Mook?

694
00:53:29,880 --> 00:53:31,360
There's nothing worrying, really.

695
00:53:36,000 --> 00:53:38,800
You were probably shocked
when the reporter made a scene that day,

696
00:53:38,880 --> 00:53:43,120
so I understand you
for dealing with the situation that way.

697
00:53:45,800 --> 00:53:48,840
Mook, you should be careful as well.

698
00:53:48,920 --> 00:53:51,240
Especially since
you're working with Mr. Thee,

699
00:53:51,880 --> 00:53:53,640
everyone's watching you.

700
00:53:54,320 --> 00:53:56,360
Your public image is very important.

701
00:53:56,880 --> 00:53:59,080
Don't cause Mr. Thee any trouble.

702
00:54:02,400 --> 00:54:03,680
Don't you worry.

703
00:54:04,320 --> 00:54:06,080
I know what I'm doing.

704
00:54:07,920 --> 00:54:09,320
I'm full. If you'll excuse me.

705
00:54:11,000 --> 00:54:12,040
Mook.

706
00:54:14,600 --> 00:54:17,600
If that's all you had to say,
then please excuse me.

707
00:54:17,680 --> 00:54:18,600
Enjoy your food.

708
00:54:18,680 --> 00:54:19,760
Mook!

709
00:54:39,440 --> 00:54:40,400
Mook.

710
00:54:42,520 --> 00:54:43,600
Mook.

711
00:54:43,680 --> 00:54:45,240
Mook, wait for me.

712
00:54:45,320 --> 00:54:46,800
Mook. Watch out!

713
00:54:49,160 --> 00:54:50,120
I'm so sorry.

714
00:54:53,600 --> 00:54:55,760
Let go of me. Mr. Thee, let go!

715
00:54:55,840 --> 00:54:57,760
If someone sees us,
you'll ruin your image.

716
00:54:59,440 --> 00:55:00,680
I've missed you, Mook.

717
00:55:06,320 --> 00:55:07,880
I think I made myself clear.

718
00:55:09,360 --> 00:55:10,360
I know.

719
00:55:11,960 --> 00:55:13,960
I'll stay out of you
and your daughter's lives.

720
00:55:15,680 --> 00:55:18,160
But that doesn't mean
I'll stop loving you.

721
00:55:21,800 --> 00:55:23,200
You should hurry to the meeting.

722
00:55:26,400 --> 00:55:27,920
Mook!

723
00:55:28,000 --> 00:55:29,320
Wait for me, Mook!

724
00:55:30,520 --> 00:55:31,560
Let's go, Whan.

725
00:55:50,440 --> 00:55:52,840
Mama's got work to do. Stop acting up!

726
00:55:54,280 --> 00:55:56,600
Start already! What's wrong with you?

727
00:55:56,680 --> 00:55:58,440
What should we do, Mook?

728
00:55:58,520 --> 00:56:00,040
I don't think it's going to start.

729
00:56:02,240 --> 00:56:03,040
Here's the plan.

730
00:56:03,120 --> 00:56:05,200
You go to the print shop
and finalize the artwork.

731
00:56:05,280 --> 00:56:06,400
Don't wait for me.

732
00:56:06,480 --> 00:56:09,200
I'll call a mechanic.
Once my car's fixed, I'll be right over.

733
00:56:10,040 --> 00:56:11,440
Got it. I've got it from here.

734
00:56:11,520 --> 00:56:13,320
- I'm counting on you.
- Okay.

735
00:56:14,280 --> 00:56:15,160
Go.

736
00:56:21,520 --> 00:56:24,080
What the hell? It was still fine before.

737
00:56:28,440 --> 00:56:29,520
What's up?

738
00:56:31,040 --> 00:56:31,880
Hey!

739
00:56:33,200 --> 00:56:35,880
Could be a problem
with the starter or the battery.

740
00:56:36,440 --> 00:56:37,440
Call a mechanic.

741
00:56:41,160 --> 00:56:43,360
You know, how about I drive you?

742
00:56:43,440 --> 00:56:45,720
I'll have Mr. Pitak take care of your car.

743
00:56:48,560 --> 00:56:49,720
Thank you,

744
00:56:50,800 --> 00:56:51,920
but no, thank you.

745
00:56:59,720 --> 00:57:02,440
TOR'S GARAGE

746
00:57:10,200 --> 00:57:11,920
MR. PAT

747
00:57:17,480 --> 00:57:20,880
{\an8}I see you and Mommy fighting all the time.

748
00:57:20,960 --> 00:57:23,000
{\an8}Why do you have to fight?

749
00:57:23,080 --> 00:57:25,920
{\an8}Don't you love each other anymore?

750
00:57:26,000 --> 00:57:27,800
{\an8}I-- Hey!

751
00:57:28,760 --> 00:57:30,960
{\an8}Can you stand still just for a minute?

752
00:57:34,120 --> 00:57:35,880
{\an8}Let me recharge my energy.

753
00:57:43,920 --> 00:57:45,280
{\an8}…attach their map…

754
00:57:51,040 --> 00:57:52,400
{\an8}Stay focused.

755
00:58:46,440 --> 00:58:48,720
{\an8}Subtitle translation by:
Ramil Natnitiwitaya

